BULLETIN - EAS ACTIVATION REQUESTED

 CHILD ABDUCTION EMERGENCY TEXAS DEPARTMENT OF PUBLIC SAFETY RELAYED BY NATIONAL WEATHER SERVICE AUSTIN/SAN ANTONIO TX 944 PM CDT FRI SEP 17 2021 

THE FOLLOWING MESSAGE IS TRANSMITTED AT THE REQUEST OF THE TEXAS DEPARTMENT OF PUBLIC SAFETY. THIS IS A CHILD ABDUCTION ALERT ISSUED BY THE TEXAS AMBER ALERT NETWORK. THE JUDSON I S D POLICE DEPARTMENT IS SEARCHING FOR ALHEIRIE RODRIGUEZ POMALES, HISPANIC, FEMALE, 12 YEARS OLD, 5 FOOT ZERO INCHES, 100 POUNDS, BROWN HAIR, BROWN EYES, AND WEARING A BLACK PULLOVER SHIRT, BLACK PANTS, CARRYING A PINK AND GRAY BACKPACK. POLICE ARE LOOKING FOR MARIE RODRIGUEZ POMALES, HISPANIC, FEMALE, 28 YEARS OLD, 5 FOOT ZERO INCHES, 120 POUNDS, BROWN HAIR, BROWN EYES IN CONNECTION WITH HER ABDUCTION. THE SUSPECT WAS LAST HEARD FROM IN CONVERSE, TX. LAW ENFORCEMENT OFFICIALS BELIEVE THIS CHILD TO BE IN GRAVE OR IMMEDIATE DANGER. IF YOU HAVE ANY INFORMATION REGARDING THIS ABDUCTION, CALL THE JUDSON ISD POLICE DEPARTMENT AT 2 1 0 6 5 9 9 7 8 9. THE NEWS MEDIA POINT OF CONTACT IS JUDSON ISD POLICE DEPARTMENT AT 2 1 0 6 5 9 9 7 8 9. $$
